Colin,

Very nice work, I'm looking forward to pretty pictures :)

Would you like me to link to your software page from the various
NEAT-related or NN-related pages that I control?  It's just a question
of whether you feel comfortable releasing it to the general public yet
or if you want to hold off.  In general, NEAT packages linked from our
pages are downloaded several hundred times a year.  I'm sure there are
people out there who would appreciate a C# version.

ken

--- In neat@yahoogroups.com, Colin Green <cgreen@d...> wrote:
> SharpNEAT, a C# .Net implementation of NEAT now has a rudamentary
web 
> site where you can download the current source code and .Net
binaries.  
> There is also a brief set of questions and answers that explain
what 
> it's all about and where it's going. There are no pretty graphs or 
> pictures as of yet,  following discussions on the group this area
is
